om/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/matty-healy-julian-casablancas.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/matty-healy-julian-casablancas-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/matty-healy-julian-casablancas-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/matty-healy-julian-casablancas-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/matty-healy-julian-casablancas-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/matty-healy-julian-casablancas-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-strokes">The Strokes</a> &#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/julian-casablancas">Julian Casablancas</a> has shared his thoughts on <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-1975">The 1975</a> &#39;s recent controversy in Malaysia that saw them banned for taking a stance on LGBTQ matters on stage.</p><p> Last weekend, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-1975-good-vibes-festival-malaysia-set-cut-short-matty-healy-criticises-anti-lgbtq-laws-kiss-bassist-3471738">The 1975&#39;s set at Good Vibes Festival in Kuala Lumpur was cut short</a> – and later, the rest of the festival was cancelled – after frontman <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/matty-healy">Matty Healy</a> criticised anti-LGBTQ laws and kissed bassist Ross MacDonald onstage.</p><p> During their headline performance on Friday (July 21), Healy called out the Malaysian government and said: “I do not see the point of inviting The 1975 to a country and then telling us who we can have sex with.”</p><p> Since then, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-1975-banned-from-malaysia-good-vibes-festival-cancelled-matty-healy-3471893">The 1975 have been banned from performing in the country</a> , and <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/malaysian-lgbtq-community-condemn-the-1975s-matty-healy-over-kiss-incident-3472125">the frontman has received backlash from Malaysia&#39;s LGBTQ+ community</a> , claiming that his actions undermined years of action by local activists.</p><p> The 1975 are now also potentially <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-1975-malaysia-good-vibes-festival-cancelled-class-action-lawsuit-artists-vendors-3473217">facing a class action lawsuit by Malaysian artists and festival vendors</a> over the festival&#39;s cancellation. </p><figure id="attachment_3473221" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3473221" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3473221" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/the-1975-matty-healy-ross-macdonald-credit-Shirlaine-Forrest-getty-images.jpg" alt="Matty Healy and Ross Macdonald of The 1975" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/the-1975-matty-healy-ross-macdonald-credit-Shirlaine-Forrest-getty-images.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/the-1975-matty-healy-ross-macdonald-credit-Shirlaine-Forrest-getty-images-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/the-1975-matty-healy-ross-macdonald-credit-Shirlaine-Forrest-getty-images-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/the-1975-matty-healy-ross-macdonald-credit-Shirlaine-Forrest-getty-images-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/the-1975-matty-healy-ross-macdonald-credit-Shirlaine-Forrest-getty-images-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/the-1975-matty-healy-ross-macdonald-credit-Shirlaine-Forrest-getty-images-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3473221" class="wp-caption-text"> Matty Healy and Ross Macdonald of The 1975 performing at Parklife Festival 2023. Credit: Shirlaine Forrest/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> The Strokes&#39; Casablancas, who was unable to perform at Good Vibes Festival with his band, <a href="https://www.nme.com/en_asia/news/music/the-strokes-good-vibes-festival-cancelled-replacement-show-malaysia-kuala-lumpur-julian-casablancas-3472345">shared on social media this weekend that they are currently working on a way to perform in Malaysia</a> .</p><p> The frontman then elaborated on his thoughts regarding the controversy in an <a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/CvBQHpAJD5C/?igshid=MzRlODBiNWFlZA==" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Instagram</a> reply, writing: “it def helped the white outsider awareness yes, for sure… i felt the same. had no idea. but when you look into it, it likely will change little to nothing in Malaysia. it&#39;s like saying you helped awareness of injustices in n korea … not one of those situations where twitter pressure&#39;s gonna work, they don&#39;t care, govt is intense there.”</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="es" dir="ltr"> Los fans del Matty Healy atacando a Julian solo por escupir verdades. <a href="https://t.co/iWp1n8Yw2U">pic.twitter.com/iWp1n8Yw2U</a></p><p> — Fernanda Torres (@MaferGooner) <a href="https://twitter.com/MaferGooner/status/1682983403266646017?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">July 23, 2023</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p> In another comment, Casablancas went into more depth about his thoughts, acknowledging that he thinks Healy meant “a positive thing”, initially agreeing it was “good to raise awareness”. But he said one should “be knowledgeable and respectful toward the culture you&#39;re not familiar with”.</p><p> He went on: “many thing to fix but we should be strategic was all… wasn&#39;t commenting on the thing – just an outider [sic] thinking it would make any difference in Malaysia… it appears to have more negative consequences… your nit [sic] allowed to show straight public kissing affection there i believe… it&#39;s a different world not his job to come fix then bail… if he stayed and went to jail then damn, respect. but i think he just made a joke/ laughted [sic] and flew home first class imm guessing.”</p><p> The musician continued to clarify his thoughts, sharing that “taking things out of context” and suggesting “julian angry at so and so” is a “prime example of internet perpetuation mass ignorance”.</p><p> In another comment, Casablancas said that he thought “defending him as heroic was a bit white”.</p><p> The 1975 also <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-1975-cancel-indonesia-taiwan-banned-malaysia-3471980">cancelled their Indonesia and Taiwan shows after getting banned from Malaysia</a> , while, as of Tuesday (July 25) <a href="https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2023/07/25/the-1975-left-country-even-before-report-lodged-against-them-says-deputy-igp#cxrecs_s" target="_blank" rel="noopener">18 police reports</a> have been filed over the incident.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-strokes-julian-casablancas-shares-his-thoughts-on-the-1975s-malaysia-lgbtq-controversy-3473769">The Strokes&#39; Julian Casablancas shares his thoughts on The 1975&#39;s Malaysia LGBTQ controversy</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
 'Baldur's Gate 3' automatically puts players at risk of a 400% spike in damage https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/baldurs-gate-3-automatically-puts-players-at-risk-of-a-400-spike-in-damage-3473761?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=baldurs-gate-3-automatically-puts-players-at-risk-of-a-400-spike-in-damageImogen Donovan Wed, 26 Jul 2023 14:08:36 +0000 Gaming NewsNewsPCPlayStation 5PS5 https://www.nme.com/?p=3473761 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/baldurs-gate-3-karmic-dice-first-playthrough.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/baldurs-gate-3-karmic-dice-first-playthrough.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/baldurs-gate-3-karmic-dice-first-playthrough-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/baldurs-gate-3-karmic-dice-first-playthrough-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/baldurs-gate-3-karmic-dice-first-playthrough-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/baldurs-gate-3-karmic-dice-first-playthrough-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/baldurs-gate-3-karmic-dice-first-playthrough-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> This setting is said to be a &quot;massive penalty&quot; to players</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/baldurs-gate-3-automatically-puts-players-at-risk-of-a-400-spike-in-damage-3473761">&#39;Baldur&#39;s Gate 3&#39; automatically puts players at risk of a 400% spike in damage</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/baldurs-gate-3-karmic-dice-first-playthrough.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/baldurs-gate-3-karmic-dice-first-playthrough.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/baldurs-gate-3-karmic-dice-first-playthrough-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/baldurs-gate-3-karmic-dice-first-playthrough-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/baldurs-gate-3-karmic-dice-first-playthrough-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/baldurs-gate-3-karmic-dice-first-playthrough-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/baldurs-gate-3-karmic-dice-first-playthrough-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/games/baldurs-gate-iii"><em>Baldur&#39;s Gate 3</em></a> &#39;s Karmic Dice is a feature that might put the player at risk of suffering a major spike in enemy damage outputs, and fortunately, players are sharing a guide on how to switch this off.</p><ul><li> <strong>READ MORE: <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/gaming-features/boss-level-2023-frankie-ward-3469756">Frankie Ward is an esports icon</a></strong></li></ul><p> Via <em><a href="https://www.gamesradar.com/this-hidden-baldurs-gate-3-setting-puts-you-at-risk-of-taking-400-extra-damage-but-you-can-disable-it/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GamesRadar</a></em> , players akdavidxy and Havelok <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/BaldursGate3/comments/159ss0q/reminderturn_off_karmic_dice_at_launchwhy_400/?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=web2x&amp;context=3" target="_blank" rel="noopener">worked together</a> in the game&#39;s subreddit to alert new <em>Baldur&#39;s Gate 3</em> fans that this setting will be active at the start of their playthroughs. Karmic Dice alters the outcome of the next dice roll in a sequence when the rolls have consistently failed, allowing the player to succeed in that specific situation.</p><blockquote class="reddit-embed-bq" style="height:316px" ><p> <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/BaldursGate3/comments/159ss0q/reminderturn_off_karmic_dice_at_launchwhy_400/">REMINDER:Turn off Karmic Dice at launch.Why? +400% Enemy Dmg</a><br /> by <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/Havelok">u/Havelok</a> in <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/BaldursGate3/">BaldursGate3</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://embed.reddit.com/widgets.js" charset="UTF-8"></script></p><p> While this appears to be a beneficial fix, Karmic Dice affects the dice rolls for enemies too. The data from akdavidxy&#39;s investigation, who was using a high armor class of 23, showed that enemies even in the early stages of <em>Baldur&#39;s Gate 3</em> attacked them with around a 30 to 40 per cent chance.</p><p> “The higher your [armor class] is, the more critical hits [you] take, and since crits do double damage, the effect of this in terms of damage is actually two times as strong,” explained akdavidxy. As such, Karmic Dice was deemed to be a “massive penalty” on players who are choosing a defensive character for their strategy.</p><p> In order to circumvent this and have a “somewhat fair” experience, players advised recent <em>Baldur&#39;s Gate 3</em> recruits to switch this setting off. Moreover, the game&#39;s creative director recommended that <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/baldurs-gate-3-director-offers-advice-on-which-character-to-play-first-3473083">newcomers should create their own character</a> rather than play as one of the origins.</p><p> “They work better if you&#39;ve played the game already once because then you see it through their eyes. What was Shadowheart thinking the first time she saw you? And now you know when you&#39;re in their head,” <a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/larian-studios">Larian Studios</a> &#39; Swen Vincke explained.</p><p> In other gaming news, <a href="https://www.nme.com/games/old-school-runescape"><em>Old School RuneScape</em></a> &#39;s <em>Desert Treasure 2 – The Fallen Empire</em> is <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/old-school-runescape-quest-desert-treasure-gets-a-sequel-after-18-years-3473743">the “most ambitious” quest to date</a> , and it&#39;s live now.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/baldurs-gate-3-automatically-puts-players-at-risk-of-a-400-spike-in-damage-3473761">&#39;Baldur&#39;s Gate 3&#39; automatically puts players at risk of a 400% spike in damage</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
